          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A radioactive beam of 59Cu was produced and",
                "accelerated using the superconducting LINAC to 6.7A",
                "MeV. The beam then passed through an ionization",
                "chamber, filled with isobutane gas, operated at two",
                "pressures, 19.5 and 10 Torr, leading to two different",
                "beam energies at the center of the H2 target. The",
                "energy loss of the beam measured in this ionization",
                "chamber provided an event-by-event identification of",
                "the 59Cu incident beam and its contaminant 59Co",
                "throughout the experiment. Ionization chamber",
                "operation at these two pressures resulted in",
                "laboratory energies of Elab = 238.7 and 278.5 MeV,",
                "corresponding to center-of-mass energies of Ecm =",
                "4.0+-0.4 MeV and 4.68+-0.25 MeV at the center of the",
                "H2 target, respectively. The average beam",
                "intensities were ~7.4*10**3 pps and 1.09*10**4 pps",
                "for the 4.0+-0.4 MeV and 4.68+-0.25 MeV runs,",
                "respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD",
                "CSICR",
                "TELES"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Protons and alpha-particles from",
                "reactions were detected using annular arrays of 100",
                "microm thick single-sided silicon strip detectors",
                "followed by a layer of 12 mm thick CsI(Tl) detectors,",
                "placed 15.5 cm downstream of the target. This",
                "detector combination served as an energy-loss and",
                "total energy (E) telescope for identifying the p and",
                "alpha-particle recoils after the target. Any",
                "background contributions from reactions on the Ag",
                "foil were subtracted by using data without the H2",
                "target, i.e., for beam impinging on the Ag foil",
                "alone. The detector telescope covered scattering",
                "angles of thetalab = 18-40 degrees."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The beam impinged on a thin windowless solid hydrogen",
                " (H2) reaction target with a 4.5 microm thick Ag foil",
                "backing facing upstream of the H2 layer. The target",
                "cell with the foil was cooled to ~4 K, and hydrogen",
                "gas was sprayed on the cooled Ag foil, which made a",
                "frozen/solid H2 target. The energy of the beam",
                "elastically scattered from the Ag foil was measured",
                "using a downstream silicon strip detector, providing",
                "continuous measurement of the target thickness during",
                "the experiment. The average target thicknesses were",
                "60.6 and 37.0 microm for the 4.0 and 4.68 MeV data",
                "collection, respectively. At these energies, the open",
                "reaction channels were (p,p), (p,p'), and (p,alpha)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Direct measurement of 59Cu(p,alpha) using a",
                "radioactive 59Cu beam at TRIUMF. The dE-E correlation",
                "provided clear identification of the protons and",
                "alpha-particles."
              ]
            }
          ],
